reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Carbon free (battery free) wireless doorbell
reviews.reviewText: When our wired doorbell failed, we tried a battery powered simple wireless button. Alas, we discovered that while winterized, wireless buttons with batteries don't like Minnesota winters. We found this little gem that uses the motive force of the "button" itself to generate power and trigger the bell. Same exact idea as the battery operated button system. Arrived just in time for our first below 14F day, and operates like champ. The button is actually not a button, but a lever masquerading as a button. Would benefit from a sticker showing where to push. Ingenious design

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just What We Needed
reviews.reviewText: When we moved to our new house, we didn’t realize there was no doorbell. However, our security system had a door bell system, but we had to install it on the side wall in order to wire it for use. That meant the people coming to the door wouldn’t see it necessarily and would knock on the door. And if you’re at the back of the house or out back, there’s no way you could hear it. So getting these little stickers was a great option to put on the door which at least alerts people to look for the doorbell. I’m glad it came as a three pack, because we will be painting the outside of the house and then we will have an extra one at least to put up after the clean coats of paint have been put on.
